messages.content: 18.5: Hello/Goodbye

You all wake up in a dimly lit hallway. Yes, ‚Äúyou all‚Äù, we‚Äôre going second person here. It feels quite narrow and suffocating, but still somehow provides plenty of room for the 9 of you.

At one end of the hallway is a window. At the other end is a poster of someone‚Äôs face with a knife driven into it.

There are six doors, three on each side. Each has a piece of paper pinned to the wall adjacent to them with images and text.
Erica Furuda gets up on shaky legs and looks around at everyone with a confused expression. "Where... Am I?"
can joliene stand
No.
Joliene does not stand.
Klaud looks around at everyone, though only briefly letting himself acknowledge Erica. "Is the Antarctica Project not over? Why are we transferring again?"
~~Theseus~~ *I* rise to my feet, hand braced against my head. I grit my teeth. "What are.. you all?" I don't understand what's happening. Or why everyone's here. Or what they're doing, ugh.
"Fuck. FUCK! I didn't get to everyone in time." I sit up and put my hand on my mouth. "Lets see. Rikarasu, Voreverl, Viotto, Erica. Not a lot to work with, and not the ones I'm looking for."

Voreverl glances around, taking in the scenery, visibly processing the situation. As she does, a grin rises to her face. "Gweheheh... So, we're not done just yet, huh?" She springs up. "Welcome, minions and enemies of Voreverl Leocot!"
"Oh, holy father of... ugh."
I don't say anything. I just wrap my arms around my torso and try not to look at her.
**MBMJ wakes up.** "Hmmm.... I must introduce myself again. I don't believe we've been acquainted. I'm Mr. Big Man Jr.... and now I'm serious goose."

"I'm not sure where Rikarasu went, and I'm definitely sure I won't get anything from... them." I stare longingly at the stocky gray-haired girl I believe I've met before and the rather slender, almost anorexic woman that looks like... them.
Joliene looks around, and through the less-than-stellar lighting, determines to be the blade-pierced poster to be the most interesting thing in the room. She inspects that closer.
The person is identifiable as Bruna Unno.

Voreverl snaps her fingers. "Those who wish to survive under my regime will follow my lead. We're breaking out of here, I don't have time to play by the rules of this project any longer!" She marches up and down the hallway as she speaks, reading the labels next to each door.
Who?
I think you met her once? Oh well.

I stand up after everyone has already gotten their bearings, slowly and silently. It doesn't shock me that I'm here again, but it doesn't put a smile on my face, either. Perhaps I can just wait for somebody to come out and monologue at me until this is over with again.
((Roll a d6))
"Oh... It's all of you. So I succeeded. The Antarctica Project is back. That's good... I must've set all of this up." Erica follows Voreverl.
"Gh..." I say, gritting my teeth. "I. Suppose breaking out is ideal." I try to continue not looking at her as I say this.

The first piece of paper Voreverl reads has the following written on it:

> **‚ÄúThe Culprit‚Äù**
> 
> Character Info: Lunatic terrorizing Klaud‚Äôs school and the surrounding area. Kills people because they‚Äôre insane. Could have a real name, but that‚Äôs not important. Keeps the principal on his toes.
> 
> Gender: Male(?)
> 
> Aesthetic: Dark clothes.
> 
> Inspirations: The Joker. That one fucking character Uchikoshi keeps trying to do. Korekiyo Shinguji. Gamzee Makara.
*Fainda, or Rikarasu, who was obscured slumped down in a corner, awakens and pushes herself up to her feet.* "...Where am I? Am I dreaming?"

So, he finally wakes up. That slender, sticklike old geezer. He doesn't strike me as a powerful type but he definitely seems like he seems like he has some fitness left into him. He definitely reads as the man who's done a sick pirouette.
"It's fantastic I can be ran into you again, for this is excellent for my research. I am doing... character work."
I wave to him.
"I would like to talk to you for a moment."
"Yes. You. The old guy."
Joliene takes a deep breath.
"The Culprit... sounds like my kinda lunatic. Schools are really so out of date in their curriculum. Doesn't prepare kids for my evil empire at all, just shortsighted."
I look around uncomfortably, trying to tune out the incessant noise so I can focus on the request. "What is it? What do we need to talk about?"
"Rikarasu!!! Who's the culprit?" Erica calls out to Rikarasu about this. "You're supposed to be a detective, right?"
*She tries to discern the situation out from all of the noise.* "Erica? You're really not dead?"

I sort of stagger off to the side. There are so many people here, I don't really understand why.. or how, or... this is stupid. I know how to navigate these situations. I should not be losing my composure for such infantile reasons, a coagulation of noise, of sound...
"Erica... why does that sound familiar?" She motions to the blonde girl. "Is that this chick?"

Klaud walks over to the paper and looks at it. "The culprit... I don't know anyone like that. Especially no one who could be described as similar to the joker." Klaud hopes it's the janitor somehow. A character that has never come up outside of Klaud's hatred for him.

I stumble to the first person I know who I don't, uh... who I don't feel the need to, um. Something. A thing, surrounding them. I walk to the wrestler, is what I mean. MBMJ. I don't *hide behind him,* to clarify, I just stand adjacent to him.
"Are you serious, Voreverl? Whatever." Erica Culbasko has no reason to care.
Joliene's eyes make a half-circle over the room, vacantly.

"What are you talking about? Is this some kind of elaboration on the bit where you pretended I hit on you for noooo reason in the middle of a climactic fight with everyone around just because I didn't approve of killing people for no reason? Because it's not funny."
Voreverl moves onto the next door's label and reads that.
"What has everyone been up to? I need to know what happened after they wrestled the queen and found out all the answers!"
"Little to many....... I have odd power that may strike many a fancy. I was never able to use them properly. After all, I was held back from the fear that I could never be who I've wanted to be."
((Roll another d6, sure.))
"I need to create my masterpiece!
"...But now I know who I am. And I know what I can do with my power. Viotto, would you mind doing a piroeutte for me?"
My head hurts so much. Too many sources of input. This incomprehensible person may give me something to latch onto, at least, no?
I do a hopefully impressive pirouette. It's half-hearted at best, and my motions likely come off as stiff and mechanical. I'm not as young as I once was, throwing these out as if it were nothing.
Klaud attempts to take the paper that mentions him off the door if this is possible. Is this allowed?
((Actually it should've been d5. Whatever.))
Sure.

"This is... Voreverl... and Viotto... and Erica... and Klaud Reaction, and 'Intuition Overdrive', and... Joliene? Bruna?" *She looks at the blue man and at Horatius.* "And... you two... 'Mr. Big Man Jr.', and... what's your name?"

The next paper Voreverl reads. 

> **Alicia Matel**
> 
> Character Info: Rikarasu‚Äôs neighbor. American tourist, in nature/vibe, but living here indefinitely. Acts like a rather dim-witted and shallow valley girl, basically, just one that‚Äôs a weeaboo.
> 
> Gender: Female
> 
> Aesthetic: Feminine clothing. Need to research fashion, particularly as it exists in Japan. Maybe gyaru influence?
> 
> Inspirations: Sort of a stock character. Like, the concept of a Mean Girl, but she isn‚Äôt that mean. Cordelia Chase. Junko Enoshima (prologue only). Token American character. She should have a soft side, maybe? Or seem interesting. Needs to ideally evoke the same desire to protect as someone like Maya Fey and all her equivalents. Not sure if Rikarasu is receptive to that, but it‚Äôs worth leaving as an option.

No reason to care. Just an endless sequence of events happening, strung together mindlessly with no cohesion or clarity. A parade that doesn't stop. Nothing worth celebrating. I hug myself tighter. I keep myself in place.
"It says he keeps the principal on his toes. The principal... That was Bruce Praxis. He was from Arctica, I think he told me... I guess this might be about that, if that's a hint to anyone?"
I turn to the woman who has addressed me. Almost everyone knows my name. I don't think I can get away with obscurity. "Theseus Rowe."
"Gweh. Seems like these papers are getting less interesting." Voreverl balls up the Alicia Matel paper and tosses it away. "Let's go through the joker one." She opens the The Culprit door.
The door is locked.
*Fainda picks up the Alicia paper and reads it.*
"Minions! Unlock this door! Immediately!"
A limp-fingered hand finds itself dragging over the side of Joliene's face, tugging down on the skin of her cheek.
"What?" *She stares down at the paper, then after a little while balls it up again and pockets it forcefully.*
I stay where I am.
"How? It's obviously a puzzle." Erica opens the door that would get a roll of 4 on the dice. Because randomness is pointless.
The door is locked.
She checks the paper, I mean.
*On this note, Fainda now searches through her possessions to try to ascertain what she has on her.*
Oh, alright.
Klaud approaches Rikarasu. "Does yours have anything in common with the page on the culprit?"
"What page?"
*She seems disoriented.*
Klaud shows her the paper talking about the culprit.

The one Erica checks:

> ~~Erikka Avdol~~ 
> Ad-hoc identities to keep track of:
> - scipe, obviously
> - Madakoe. Regrettably.
> - BP
> - stupid brazil nonsense
> - Cogito (not that one)
> - Kyouzou (not my fault)
> - X
> - Eric uses an account called zeeteedeefan 
> - Autumn
> - Ariadne
> - ‚ÄúThe Overseer‚Äù
> 
> Entering Arctica physically is still a non-option. Don‚Äôt want to risk it.
*She reads the paper on 'The Culprit' and thinks.* "...It's the same format."

As the blond girl takes over reading paper duties, Voreverl looks for other clues, at which moment she notices the poster of Bruna. "Ah, that's... gweh..." She makes her way over to it, and attempts to pull the knife out of the wall.
You can do that, sure.
She rolls up the poster, then pockets both it and the knife.
You can do that, sure.
((do i assume we all start here with nothing on us))
"You shouldn't do that. You shouldn't take the knife."
Your clothes and the PDAs (inactive), I guess.
"Madakoe? Brazil? scipe...? I know most of these. Even zeeteedeefan contacted me about you once, Voreverl. I think this one is my paper?" Erica takes it off as well.
I get closer to the doors. Do any of the images look familiar to me..?
Actually, you can just have whatever you would've had on you. Sure.
((would've had on earth or arctica?))
Voreverl glares at Joliene. "Why? 'Fraid I'm gonna take revenge? Gweheheh... Don't worry, I've satisfied my bloodlust, for now."

I'm becoming increasingly sick to my stomach, in addition to the head pain. Why does this matter? Why am I in this cacophonous reminder of what once was? I've changed, I've moved beyond this, I know I have. I'm a new man. I can't be dragged back into the same swamp I once drained, as if it were nothing. 
"Could you all... just wait? Just, give me a minute? Please? I have shown you all empathy across our time together... maybe, a small bit in return would not be the worst thing. I just... need some quiet. Please. Can you wait five minutes to solve this puzzle, to tear apart this room? Only five minutes?"
"...no, actually. I'm... not sure why."
"Please."
*Fainda walks towards Viotto.* "I agree. We need time to work through this together."
Oh, right, I said images, didn't I? Most you don't recognize. That part doesn't matter. Just inspiration material. Or whatever.
"Huh? Zeety D Fan? Can I see that?"
"What are you agreeing with? I didn't... say that. I need a lull in the conversation, I need a moment."
"Is that impossible?"
"Like Bolsonaro!"
She holds it out for Voreverl. "Something about an Eric. The title says Erikka though, so I guess it's supposed to be like 2 sides of me?"
It's impossible.
Theseus... I don't shut up. I don't stop moving forwards. I pull down a sheet of paper to read the words.
No one gives Viotto a moment, even as he lies about having ever acted with empathy. Sad!
"...What?"
"How the fuck are you this pathetic?....."
"Was... was my pirouette that bad? I'm sorry..."
"No, it was good- but"
"I am truly sorry."
The pirouette was middling.
"This is your neighbour, right? What was she like? Was she some kind of persona? I mean... If they're talking about inspirations these people can't be acting 100% naturally."
"Look, I want to talk you. You can apologize by talking to me."
"I am. I am talking to you. What is the conversation topic?"
"What are we talking about?"

*She puts on her best voice of confidence as she addresses Viotto Entenmann, taking a few glances at Intuition Overdrive in the meanwhile.* "The conversation is in disarray due to... the suddenness of the circumstances we have been placed in. If we work together, we can help guide the conversation into a position of effectiveness."
"Will you work with me?"
I examine the paper.
Just a random one, then?
"This... no, this obviously isn't you. You're not related to Avdol, right? It's... then... it says entering Arctica is... Cogito was... Autumn was... *Kyouzou* was...?" Voreverl starts to feel dizzy.
Just a random one. We can say the one closest to me, sure.
"Autumn is a month." Erica rolls her eyes.

> **Eric Zeety**
> 
> Character Info: Voreverl‚Äôs friend. Works at the zoo with her. Incredibly receptive to her wild schemes and whims. Basically a doormat.
> 
> Gender: Male
> 
> Aesthetic: Bald. Or shaved. Not sure if those words are technically exclusive? Covers this up with a beanie. Dressed in casual clothes otherwise.
> 
> Inspirations: Think Eric from ZTD, basically. That‚Äôs literally the name. Or any sort of desperate incel character. The reporter from Megamind, or whatever. But without a villain twist. Eric shouldn‚Äôt leave this role unless something goes very wrong.
*She looks at Klaud.* "...She was no different than me or you, entirely normal."

"N-no! I will not work with you! I object to the concept of the work on the face of it! We can't get any farther by solving mysteries, by opening doors. Haven't we tried for long enough? Guiding the conversation... you couldn't do that if you tried. Don't talk down to me."
I blink at the sheet of paper. This isn't relevant to me.
"I think we should both go to a quiet, concentrated area to talk about this."
...I walk over to Voreverl. That girl. Until I'm facing her.
*Fainda scowls.* "You evidently have changed little, Viotto Entenmann."
Voreverl glances at Theseus for a moment. "Go away, I'm doing something important. Madakoe... that was... with the girl that time..."
"I know who Madakoe is."
"Then why are they talking about inspirations? Obviously people are going to be inspired by things around them, but that seems impossible to actually keep track of."
I don't listen to the words she's saying. It's all so irritating... I shove the piece of paper at her.
Joliene wheels to a comparatively quieter part of the room.
There's no logical gain from me doing it. I don't understand.
*She seems to think, but doesn't answer.*
Voreverl snatches it. "What *is* it?" She reads over it annoyedly before her expression switches to complete focus.

"Madakoe Angiot is a fictional character I kin. I used to project hallucinations of him around me with magic to pretend I had a friend because I was mentally ill. But I'm over it now." Erica states this confidently. "He did seem to know more than me though. In more ways than even I pretended. He told me a lot of secrets about the Antarctica project."
I cross my arms over my torso again. I want to tell her to stop fucking posturing, but no words take form or purpose. My mouth is dry. I lean back against the wall.
*Fainda turns and stares at Erica.* "What?"
"Did you just say... Madakoe Angiot was a projected hallucination?"
How many pieces of paper are left?
"Yes? I mean he was around before I had magic but no one could see him then."
*She scoffs, seeming to mock the proposition.* "How could you possibly be skilled enough with magic to perform such a feat indetectibly?"
I think it should be two not read by anyone at this point?
"D-does anyone here know a, uh... scipe, BP, X, Ariadne, or 'The Overseer'?"
I take one of those and read it.
"I know of an X, yes."
I flinch at the fourth word Voreverl says. Violently.
Erica raises her hand. "I'm scipe. Madakoe told me to be at one point."
It's noticeable to everyone in the room.
*She recognises the name scipe, but keeps her lips shut.*
*She walks towards Voreverl.* "...Are you okay?"

> **GassyNTricky**
> 
> Character Info: Erica‚Äôs online associate. Loves the character ‚ÄúGas Trick‚Äù and is vocal about this, using images of him and speech patterns he does. All in all, a complete joke of a character.
> 
> Gender: NB maybe but Erica will presume male so this doesn‚Äôt matter
> 
> Aesthetic: Doesn‚Äôt matter. Unlikely to be seen physically.
> 
> Inspirations: Gas Trick, obviously. The fucking ‚Äúthis is the third week in a row you‚Äôve shown such and such‚Äù meme. Erica herself, in a weird way. Daru S;G. Okonogi. Concept of a HS conversation.
What is anyone even talking about.
I walk over to the girl I know is named Erica.
"Jeh mentioned an overseer program to me once. I don't think it's a person though, so it might be unrelated."
"This is fantastic information!"
"What?"
I shove the piece of paper at her.
"Gweh? Y-yeah, Voreverl Leocot is just... facing some confusion..." She swallows hard. "I'm, uh, trying to... reach out to others a bit more... so, good job asking, minion."

"There is none. If you find one, come tell me, ha! But it's clear at this point, isn't it? Why we were brought here, and why we were brought together before. It was to prevent that mystical area from existing. You all cannot help yourselves. You cannot stop yourselves from speaking out for one moment. That is the commonality here. I've worked it out. I may believe myself to have more purpose in it than others, but perhaps I, too, have this same addiction. None of us... none of us can wait. None of us can slow down. None of us can abandon our purpose for one second to allow for any peace. We are all our own hell. That is assuredly the message our captors meant to communicate, don't you think? But I... I am not a slave to my programming. I am done. I win."
I step over to a wall, slump down, and shut up.
*She smiles.* "I see. Voreverl Leocot, can I count on you to work with me?"

She takes it. "Oh, yeah... GassyNTricky was some kind of roleplayer who liked breaking bad or something? He was... I mean..." Erica holds back a few more direct emotional outbursts. "I don't know. I kind of avoided dwelling on it."

I'm not helping myself, by acting this way. Even I can see how obviously stupid and bitter and curled-in on myself I am. The fact that no word escapes me, that there's zero verbal posturing that can free me from this ffffuuucking situation... I'm stuck here.
She smirks back. "That depends on your goal. If it serves my evil scheme, there's nothing that can stop me."

~~Oh, fuck yes. Did you hear that guys? Viotto is going to shut up. That's amazing.~~

The place remains eerily silent beyond whatever is said by one of the nine here.
"All bark and no bite, huh? Seems like your character. No matter how you try, your just as much as a lazy bum as that Sheeval character."
Eerily silent beyond the lack of silence, of course. How true.
Klaud goes and reads the final paper.
Alright, Klaud.
"Can't you see that I'm trying to help people? I'm doing exactly what my mom has done. To fix and set what's right.... I want to help you, I genuinely do, so can you-"
*She addresses Voreverl further.* "I shall unite us so as to be able to deduce our way through this situation together. Through this, we can escape and your schemes may flourish.*

Klaud reads the final one.
> **Currer Bell**
> 
> Character Info: Lives in the same city as Viotto. Potential conversation partner for his nonsense. The name might be a bit much? Beliefs can change depending on the argument, but maybe gravitate towards more libertarian vibes to placate racism or whatever while still having things to disagree with him on. Could interact with Sheeval but this might be worth avoiding.
> 
> Gender: Female(?)
> 
> Aesthetic: Whatever clothes can be found. Practical. Doesn‚Äôt really matter.
> 
> Inspirations: The concept of real author Charlotte Bront√´. Light Yagami. Nagito Komaeda. Ayn Rand. Asshole with an ideology. 

...Bit of an anticlimax.
"...I always wished to come find and assist you."
"Viotto? This one's for you. Do you know a Currer Bell?" He holds it out for Viotto to take.
I will not respond to a clear attempt to provoke me. Sheeval's name cannot be defiled by this person. It is not so unresilient.
"No."
*Fainda goes around, gathers all of the pieces of paper, and pockets all of them.*
Joliene looks through the window.
"Gweheheh... sounds like a perfect way to prove yourself, minion. Still, I'd be shocked if you could unite some of these idiots."
Erica does not let her do this.

.........

There's

nothing outside the window.
Is it dark? Or is there nothing?
*She doesn't fight Erica.*

When my voice comes out, it's low and strained. "Intuition, I don't.. I don't think you're helping." I try to inject some of my previous levity, some amount of, like... power to it, I don't know. The intonation of the words. So things remain as they are.
Voreverl is fine letting go of her pieces of paper, since she's already read them.
Erica examines the center of the floor for some reason she is not going to explain.
*She leaves her be and walks towards Theseus, who she can perceive is quiet and seems to be struggling.* "Theseus Rowe... I am Detective Fainda Shinjitsu. Can I count on you to work with me?"
Joliene attempts to open the window.

.........

It's

pitch black.
Klaud goes around and checks if any of the doors are more receptive to being opened now that they've read the papers.
I hear their words. I hear them. "No. No. No. You're right. This is going nowhere... I'm just torturing people! Like I did to... them."
Does he just, like. Try every door?
"I need time. I need time to think about this things. I need a place to think. To think about all this, yes. Please."
Collect yourself. Collect yourself. I turn to the woman, who I remember vaguely from the group chat. I'm pretty sure that Fainda isn't her name, but it's not... whatever.
Yes.
Joliene attempts to reach through the window.
"I suppose it depends. What are you working towards?"
The window has glass. It cannot be reached through.
Can it be opened?
"The truth." *She stares at Theseus for a moment and examines their expression.* "And a resolution to this situation for you."
Is there anything noteworthy or is this the first instance of a 6 room door that is not a Q&A reference. Erica's mind would be blown.
"The more things change, the more things stay the same..."
"A resolution?" I blink at her. "I don't think you're the one who gets to determine what that looks like."

When Klaud tries the final door, the click it makes is different from the others.

The ceiling is lifted up, away, beyond anyone's sight. Perhaps some sort of massive claw does so, or something? It would be mostly obscured from everyone's view.

Without the support of this roof, the walls fall over, toppling onto the ground limply. Only the wall with the window remains up.
Nothing. The floor is concrete. Not notable.
"Ah."
"As in... an escape from this place. Do you not desire that, Theseus?"
Voreverl looks around, is it all pitch black?
I sit down somewhere and think. Think harder. I must find information that I can use to help me.
Joliene glances behind herself, then turns to wheel into the expanse of nothing.
Klaud tries to check if there is a floor beyond the walls.

...Yes. Pitch black.

...Actually, there's some ethereal blue lights visible circling around, like the aurora almost. I liked that.
*Fainda turns to look around as the walls collapse. She's a little more disoriented, but doesn't say anything.*
I shift myself over until I am sitting next to Intuition.
Erica looks up at the sky. Is it really endless?
You can't see     an end.
"Gweheheh. Back here, huh? Wonder if Joe's skulking around." Voreverl's voice wavers a bit while saying that.
...I recognize that light.
Does this accomplish anything?
"...Theseus?"
"It's the void... It's the void!" Erica excitedly summons the stupid green cube again.
"..So what was with you and that fire?..." I say this to Viotto.
I consider moving back.
...There's a floor that the concrete one is resting on top of, sure. It's invisible, but Joliene doesn't just fall forever.
It's like the Aurora borealis, right? That's how I remember thinking of it... intangible, disparate. Until I stopped thinking. I remember when I stopped thinking.
A woman is talking to me. I refocus on her. "What?"
Klaud tries carefully walking onto the invisible floor to be on the other side of the window.

What?

Oh, right. You know what, fucking sure. Erica summons a cube with slightly beveled corners. But she only gets the one. If she tries it again it won't work.
"I'm in control here." Erica proudly displays the perfectly generic object.
How long was the fall? Could she even make it back into the blossomed hallway with her wheelchair?
*She tries not to get distracted from her conversation.* "Theseus, I want to help us uncover the truth and escape from this place. Will you trust and assist me?"
It's a slight bump. She can probably manage?
Well, that's nice. She doesn't try.
Alright.
Does anything happen?
Voreverl glances at the object briefly. "That's pretty lame."
She's saying something, still. "Sure." I say. Escaping sounds ideal, doesn't it..?

...The other side of the window looks into the hallway, but it's very blurry. You can see the other 8 participants through it.

...And one more person.
"Thank you."

"Well, I haven't unlocked all my powers yet. I think they're like... Memory locked for some reason." Erica rambles about things that don't matter. She isn't Viotto, so she doesn't get the excuse of dementia.
*She now looks at the green cube and walks towards Erica.* "How did you do that?"
"Guys! Someone else is in there!" Klaud calls out. Who is nearest to the other person?
Oh, I don't know. Voreverl?
The other person walks up to the window.
I wave at Klaud.

roles.name: if women are oppressed then why

messages.content: "Gweh!? Where!?" Voreverl rapidly starts spinning around and scrutinizing the scenery.
Joliene glances in Klaud's direction.
"......" I see someone.
Does she still look the same?
Voreverl can't see anyone other than the participants.
"Autumn!? ...Eric!?"

I sigh, and decide to try and give an answer, ignoring the commotion. "I understand that you're looking for some sort of reaction, here. I don't wish to provide it to you. But it's an interesting question, I suppose. It's really quite simple, in the end. I, through negligence, set fire to my clinic, and many died as a result."
I'm pleasantly surprised at how easily the story comes out. My previous attempt at writing it out on that tablet was messy, and emotional. I had thought about better ways to phrase things since then. Ways that would cause me to feel less annoyance when I look back on it.
 "There is no more complex story than that. But it surely affected the course of my life. I hadn't exactly... been a great person before then. You could say that I lacked empathy. I never thought about how my words and actions might affect others besides me. But, I was given a chance to develop it. And for that, I am grateful. Does that answer your question?"
When I look into the window, what's there?
"What are you all talking about?"
Nope.
*I look into the window too.*
Klaud, on the other side of it.
"Voreverl, can you feel around the window. Someone is waving at me from there."
Is anyone else there, other than Klaud?
Nope!
"...On it!" Voreverl feels around the window.
"...I can't see anything."
That's not true.
"Is Erica projecting a hallucination behind that window for some of you?"
Jesus. Take me out to dinner first, alright? I chuckle. Everyone can hear that, sure.

messages.content: *She snaps to look at the noise.* "Who was that?"
I walk out towards the side Klaud is on so everyone but Klaud can see my silhouette now.

messages.content: The voice is the same, right? It has to be the same.
